metadata.name: Love
metadata.description:
He locks her in a golden cage to protect her from fears and horrors. 
He forgets that the cage itself is a test. It breaks her essence. 

In the beginning, he watches her closely. Later the shackles become her continuation. 
And “the bird” doesn’t leave the cage even when the door  is opened. 

Yes, love is crazy and sometimes cruel. 
But we always expect it with a warm heart.
